P Cherry Point Refinery resolves all PHA findings, some of which result in modifications to refinery processes.  Replacement of the anhydrous ammonia tank to reduce the stored quantity to below threshold quantity is one example of such a change.  The following changes are currently planned or have been recently completed:

?    Upgrade operator shelters to blast-resistant buildings, including pressurization, alarming, and automatic shutdowns (completed); 

?    Move emergency evacuation areas to more remote locations outside of the main refinery (completed);

?    Move maintenance personnel to remote locations outside of main refining areas (completed);

?    Install emergency isolation valves on propane bullets (completed);

?    Install emergency generators; and

?    Improve drainage away from sphere containment area and install remote impoundment basin (completed).
